<div style="max-width:75%; text-align:center; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;" class="d-flex flex-column justify-content-center align-content-center text-start">
    <h1 class="p-4 my-5 custom-title" style="font-size: 80px; font-weight: 700;">Template Configuration</h1>
    <hr />
    <h4 class="mt-5 mb-4">Template will consist of html files.</h4>
    <h4 class="mb-5">To create a template for your view. you have tow ways</h4>

    <hr />
    <h2 class="my-5 custom-title">First way</h2>
    <h5 class="mb-0 mt-3">Create templates folder in you app then create inside that templates folder. create folde by app name.</h5>
    <h3 class="mb-1 mt-5 custom-color">Example</h3>
    <h5 class="mb-0 mt-3">Return render(request, 'blogs/search_results.html', context)</h5>
    <h5 class="mb-5 mt-3">Search_results.html should exists in blogs/templates/blogs/search_results.html</h5>

    <hr />
    <h2 class="my-5 custom-title">Second</h2>
    <h5 class="mb-0 mt-3">Create folder in same level with project root.</h5>
    <h5 class="mb-1 mt-2">Structure should be like that.</h5>
    <h3 class="mb-3 mt-4 custom-color">Project root:</h3>
    <pre class="mb-2">
        <code class="language-Django">
            --urls.py
            --settings.py
            app
            app
            templates
            <span></span>
        </code>
    </pre>
    <h5 class="mb-0 mt-4">In project root > settings.py</h5>
    <h5 class="mb-3 mt-2">Change TEMPLATES list into that codes.</h5>
    <pre class="mb-5">
        <code class="language-Django">
            import os
            TEMPLATES = [
                {
                    'BACKEND': 'django.template.backends.django.DjangoTemplates',
                    'DIRS': [BASE_DIR / 'templates']
                    ,
                    'APP_DIRS': True,
                    'OPTIONS': {
                        'context_processors': [
                            'django.template.context_processors.i18n',
                            'django.template.context_processors.debug',
                            'django.template.context_processors.request',
                            'django.contrib.auth.context_processors.auth',
                            'django.contrib.messages.context_processors.messages',
                        ],
                    },
                },
            ]
            <span></span>
        </code>
    </pre>

    <hr />
    <h2 class="my-5 custom-title">Example</h2>
    <div class="mt-3"></div>
    <pre>
        <code class="language-Django">
            return render(request, 'blogs/search_results.html', context)
            <span></span>
        </code>
    </pre>
    <h5 class="mb-3 mt-3">search_results.html should exists in templates/blogs/search_results.html</h5>
    <pre>
        <code class="language-Django">
            return render(request, 'search_results.html', context)
            <span></span>
        </code>
    </pre>
    <h5 class="mb-5 mt-3">search_results.html should exists in templates/search_results.html</h5>
</div>